revision.text:
'''''APCOM''''' is an important [[press agency|press agencies]] in Italy.
Founded by the Italian journalist [[Lucia Annunziata]] in 2001, is based in [[Rome, Italy]] and has offices in [[Budapest]], [[Brussels]], [[Moscow]] and [[New York City]]. Since its foundation has an exclusive partnership with [[Associated Press]] for Italy and Switzerland and in 2008 has signed an agreement with [[RIA Novosti]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.apcom.net/agenzia.shtml |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-11-06 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081019200410/http://www.apcom.net/agenzia.shtml |archivedate=2008-10-19 |df= }} {{it icon}}</ref> Is an exclusive partner in Italy of [[MINDS|MINDS International]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.apcom.net/servizi/minds.shtml |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-11-06 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081016104048/http://www.apcom.net/servizi/minds.shtml |archivedate=2008-10-16 |df= }} {{it icon}}</ref>

In 2003 was acquired by ''Telecom Media News'', a division of [[Telecom Italia Media]] and provide report and news for [[La7]] and [[MTV Italy]] news programmes, teletext and websites.

On April 29, 2009 the Italian businessman [[Giancarlo Abete]] (through ''[[Gruppo Abete]]'') has acquired a majority stake (60%) in ''Telecom Media News''.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.asca.it/news-EDITORIA__IL_GRUPPO_ABETE_SI_RAFFORZA_CON_ACQUISIZIONE_APCOM-827353-ORA-.html |title=EDITORIA: IL GRUPPO ABETE SI RAFFORZA CON ACQUISIZIONE APCOM  |publisher=[[ASCA (news agency)|ASCA]] |date=2009-04-29 |accessdate=2009-05-16 |language=Italian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.affaritaliani.it/mediatech/editoria_gruppo_abete_acquisisce_apcom140509.html |title=Editoria/ Il gruppo Abete acquisisce Apcom |publisher=[[Affari Italiani]] |date=2009-05-14 |accessdate=2009-05-16 |language=Italian}}</ref>

