[[File:brasaodealagoa.jpg|thumb|Coat-of-arms of the Barons of Alagoa]]

'''Baron of Alagoa''' ({{lang-pt|Barão de Alagoa}}) was a noble title created by D. [[Maria II of Portugal|Maria II]] by decree on 22 December 1841 in favour of [[José Francisco da Terra Brum]], a wealthy merchant from the city of [[Horta (Azores)|Horta]], in the [[Portugal|Portuguese]] archipelago of the [[Açores]]. The landowner had his residence along the margins of the ''Ribeira da Conceição'', and included properties in the so-named coastal shoreline of Alagoa (today occupied by the football field of Fayal Sport).

==List of barons/baronettes==
# [[José Francisco da Terra Brum]], 1st Baron of Alagoa;
# [[José Francisco da Terra Brum II]], 2nd Baron of Alagoa. In 1844, the title was extinguished following the death of the Baron;<ref name="Dias163">Fernando Faria Ribeiro (2007), p.163</ref>
# [[Manuel Maria da Terra Brum]], 3rd Baron of Alagoa, following his service to the communities of the [[Faial-Pico Channel]], King [[Carlos I of Portugal]] created Manuel Maria the third baron.<ref name=Dias163/>

