'''Ekwulobia Prison''' is a medium security [[prison]] in [[Aguata]] Local Government Area of [[Anambra State]]. The prison has an operational housing capacity of 85 inmates.<ref>[http://www.vanguardngr.com/2015/07/boko-haram-detainees-azodo-urges-fg-to-rescind-decision-on-relocation/ No room for Boko Haram detainees in Ekwulobia Prison]</ref>

In June 2015, it was reported that 47 [[Boko Haram]] suspects had been transferred to the prison on orders of President [[Buhari]].<ref>[http://anambrariansnews.com.ng/?p=14418 Anambra’s Boko Haram Prisoners And Buhari’s Deafening Silence]</ref><ref>[http://dailypost.ng/2015/07/05/soldiers-take-over-security-at-ekwulobia-prison/ Soldiers take over security at Ekwulobia Prison]</ref>

