{{Infobox diplomatic mission |name = High Commission of Swaziland in London |image = High Commission of Swaziland in London.jpg |caption = The High Commission with protesters |location = [[Westminster]], [[London]] |address = 20 [[Buckingham Gate, London|Buckingham Gate]], London, SW1E 6LB |coordinates = {{coord|51|29|58.1|N|0|8|23.9|W|type:landmark_region:GB-WSM|display=inline,title}} |high_commissioner = Dumsile T. Sukati }}
The '''High Commission of Swaziland''' in [[London]] is the [[diplomatic mission]] of [[Swaziland]] in the [[United Kingdom]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/263519/LDL_December_2013.pdf |title=The London Diplomatic List |date=14 December 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131211155353/https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/263519/LDL_December_2013.pdf |archivedate=11 December 2013 |df= }}</ref>
The High Commission is housed in a building designed by [[Reginald Blomfield]] in the late 19th century and features sculpture-work by [[Henry Pegram]].<ref>{{cite news | url= http://www.demotix.com/news/1099784/swaziland-vigil-high-commission-london#media-1099771 | title= 20 Buckingham Gate | date=30 November 2013}}</ref>
A regular protest has been held since 2010 each Saturday by those opposed to the rule of [[King Mswati III]].<ref>{{cite news | url= http://www.victorianweb.org/art/architecture/homes/53.html | title= Swaziland Vigil at High Commission - London | date=10 March 2012}}</ref>
