'''Independent National Alliance of Angola''' (ANIA, {{lang-pt|Aliança Nacional Independente de Angola}}) is a [[political party]] in [[Angola]]. ANIA was founded on April 11, 1995.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cne.ao/partidos.cfm|title=Comissão Nacional Eleitoral de Angola|website=www.cne.ao|access-date=2017-07-06}}</ref> The party is a member of the coalition [[New Democracy (Angola)|New Democracy]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Amundsen|first=Inge|last2=Weimer|first2=Markus|date=2008|title=Opposition Parties and the 2008 Parliamentary Elections in Angola|url=http://www.cmi.no/publications/file/?3103=opposition-parties-and-the-upcoming-2008|journal=CMI Working Paper|language=en|volume=WP 2008:9}}</ref> It is led by former [[National Liberation Front of Angola]] (FNLA) youth leader, José Fernando Fula 'Tó Zé'.<ref>http://www.multipress.info/viewnew.php?id=302</ref>

