{{Infobox Bilateral relations|Kosovan–Maldivian|Kosovo|Maldives|filetype=svg}}

'''Kosovan–Maldivian relations''' are foreign relations between [[Kosovo]]{{ref label|status|a|}} and the [[Maldives]]. Kosovo [[2008 Kosovo declaration of independence|declared its independence]] from [[Serbia]] on 17 February 2008 and the Maldives [[International recognition of Kosovo|recognised]] it on 19 February 2009.<ref>{{cite web|title=Maldives extends full diplomatic recognition to the Republic of Kosovo |url=http://www.foreign.gov.mv/v3/?p=news&view=sep&nid=3042 |publisher=Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Republic of Maldives |date=2009-02-19 |accessdate=2009-02-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722222923/http://www.foreign.gov.mv/v3/?p=news&view=sep&nid=3042 |archivedate=2011-07-22 |df= }}</ref> On the 16 April 2009, [[Kosovo]] and the Maldives established diplomatic relations with one another.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telegrafi.com/?id=2&a=4054|title=Kosova dhe Maldivet vendosin marrëdhënie diplomatike|publisher=Telegrafi|language=Albanian|date=2009-04-16|accessdate=2009-04-16}}</ref>

==Bribery Accusations==
On 7 March, the Maldivian President [[Mohamed Nasheed]] asked police to investigate the allegations of a US$2 million bribe given to Maldivian government officials to recognise Kosovo as an independent state.<ref>[http://www.minivannews.com/news_detail.php?id=6125 President orders bribery investigation] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090405010717/http://www.minivannews.com/news_detail.php?id=6125 |date=2009-04-05 }}</ref> On 17 March, [[Majlis of the Maldives|People’s Majlis]] National Security Committee launched probe into [[Islamic Democratic Party (Maldives)|Islamic Democratic Party]]'s allegations regarding the bribery.<ref>[http://www.minivannews.com/news_detail.php?id=6177 Parliament launches bribery investigation] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090322132640/http://www.minivannews.com/news_detail.php?id=6177 |date=2009-03-22 }}</ref> [[Balkan Insight]] reported that Kosovo businessman, [[Behgjet Pacolli]], who also heads the [[New Kosovo Alliance]] party, has denied any involvement in the bribery case and stated that he only lobbied for the recognition of Kosovo.<ref>[http://miadhu.com.mv/news.php?id=9605 Majlis Committee launches probe into IDP allegations on Kosovo]{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Foreign Minister [[Ahmed Shaheed]] was cross-examined by the parliamentary committee on 28 March.<ref>[http://www.minivannews.com/news_detail.php?id=6244 Parliament cross-examines foreign minister] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090413233627/http://www.minivannews.com/news_detail.php?id=6244 |date=2009-04-13 }}</ref> The police investigation was closed on 6 May 2009, concluding that there was no evidence of corruption and the diplomatic process was conducted according to international standards; the NSC investigation was suspended.<ref>{{cite web|title=No evidence of bribery in Kosovo investigation |url=http://www.minivannews.com/news_detail.php?id=6467 |publisher=Minivan News |date=2009-05-06 |accessdate=2009-07-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090529014902/http://www.minivannews.com/news_detail.php?id=6467 |archivedate=May 29, 2009 }}</ref>

==Maldivian support at the ICJ==
{{main|International Court of Justice advisory opinion on Kosovo's declaration of independence}}

The Maldives was absent at the 8 October 2008 United Nations General Assembly vote regarding an ICJ hearing on the legality of Kosovo's independence.<ref name="UN Backing Request by Serbia...">{{cite web|url=https://www.un.org/News/Press/docs/2008/ga10764.doc.htm|title=Backing Request by Serbia, General Assembly Decides to Seek International Court of Justice Ruling on Legality of Kosovo’s Independence|publisher=United Nations|date=2008-10-08|accessdate=2008-10-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=ODS Team |url=http://daccessdds.un.org/doc/UNDOC/GEN/N08/502/57/PDF/N0850257.pdf?OpenElement |title=Ods Home Page |publisher=Daccessdds.un.org |date= |accessdate=2009-04-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090920021047/http://daccessdds.un.org/doc/UNDOC/GEN/N08/502/57/PDF/N0850257.pdf?OpenElement |archivedate=2009-09-20 |df= }}</ref> On 21 April 2009, it was announced by the ICJ that the Maldives was one of the 36 UN member states to summit a written statement to the [[International Court of Justice|ICJ]] regarding the legality of Kosovo's unilaterally proclaimed independence. The Maldives written statement is in favour and supports the legality of Kosovo's independence from Serbia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.icj-cij.org/docket/files/141/15125.pdf|title=Accordance with International Law of the Unilateral Declaration of Independence by the Provisional Institutions of Self-Government of Kosovo (Request for Advisory Opinion) - Filing of written statements and of a written contribution|date=2009-04-21|publisher=International Court of Justice|accessdate=2009-04-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110605031911/http://www.icj-cij.org/docket/files/141/15125.pdf|archive-date=2011-06-05|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref><ref>[http://www.b92.net/eng/news/politics-article.php?mm=4&dd=21&yyyy=2009 "35 countries to take part in ICJ case"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110607181232/http://www.b92.net/eng/news/politics-article.php?mm=4&dd=21&yyyy=2009 |date=2011-06-07 }} ''[[B92|b92.net]]'' 21 April 2009 Link accessed 27 July 2009</ref>

The ICJ ruled that Kosovo's declaration of independence was legal.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kosovo independence declaration deemed legal|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2010/07/22/us-serbia-kosovo-idUSTRE66L01720100722|accessdate=24 September 2012|newspaper=Reuters|date=22 July 2010}}</ref>

