{{about|the defunct political grouping in Liechtenstein|general information about politicians that do not associate with parties|Independent (politician)}}

The '''Non-Party List Liechtenstein''' ({{lang-de|Überparteiliche Liste Liechtenstein}}, '''ULL''') was a political party in [[Liechtenstein]] formed to contest the [[Liechtenstein general election, 1989|1989 general election]] and prevent any of the larger parties from forming a majority. It did not reach the minimum vote threshold to gain seats in the [[Landtag of Liechtenstein|Landtag]], and subsequently dissolved in 1990.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Parties: Political landscape after 1945|url=http://www.fuerstundvolk.li/fuv/fuv.do?site=421173216f221000996d610c1957690b|work=Prince and People: Liechtenstein Civics|publisher=School Office of the Principality of Liechtenstein|year=2007|accessdate=13 February 2014|language=German}}</ref>

