'''Sacesinians''' were an ancient people who fought with for the [[Persian people|Persians]] in [[Alexander the Great]]'s [[Wars of Alexander the Great|war of conquest]] on the [[Achaemenid Empire]].  They gave horsemen to the Persians which were used together with the horsemen of [[Caucasian Albania]].  They lived in the north east of [[Armenia]] along the [[Kura (Caspian Sea)|Kura]] river.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/The_Anabasis_of_Alexander/Book_III/Chapter_VIII|title=The Anabasis of Alexander|last=Arrian}}</ref>

